'''Ashoka Trust for Research in Ecology and the Environment''' (ATREE) is a research institution founded by [[Kamaljit S. Bawa]] based in [[Bangalore]], India focusing in the areas of biodiversity conservation and sustainable development<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/content/374149/ashoka-trust-for-research-in-ecology-and-the-environment-atree/|title=Ashoka Trust for Research in Ecology and the Environment (ATREE) - India Environment Portal - News, reports, documents, blogs, data, analysis on environment & development - India, South Asia|website=Indiaenvironmentportal.org.in|accessdate=22 April 2018}}</ref>.

The trust works to generate rigorous interdisciplinary knowledge for achieving environmental conservation and sustainable development in a socially just manner, to enable the use of this knowledge by policy makers and society, and to train the next generation of scholars and leaders<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/video/karnataka/crafting-weed-wonder-666431.html|title=Crafting a weed into a wonder|date=24 April 2018|website=Deccanherlad.com|accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/bengaluru/2018/mar/31/bwssb-junks-surveys-claims-city-taps-wont-run-dry-in-summers-1795057.html|title=BWSSB junks surveys, claims city taps won’t run dry in summers|website=Newindianexpress.com|accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref>. 

The trust work in a large geographical area, including [[Western Ghats]] and the [[Himalayas]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/science/tough-terrain-saves-sikkims-high-altitude-forests/article23466429.ece|title=Tough terrain saves Sikkim’s high-altitude forests|first=Aathira|last=Perinchery|date=7 April 2018|accessdate=22 October 2018|website=Thehindu.com}}</ref>.

