{{Infobox building | name = Slovak radio | native_name = | native_name_lang = <!-- images --> | logo = | logo_size = | logo_caption = | image = Upside down Pyramid, Bratislava 02.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = <!-- map --> | map_type = | pushpin_relief = | image_map = | map_caption = <!-- location --> | location = | address = | location_city = | location_country = Slovakia | coordinates = {{coord|48|9|15|N|17|6|51|E|display=inline,title}} <!-- stats --> | former_names = | alternate_names = | etymology = | status = | cancelled = | topped_out = | building_type = [[Buildings]] | architectural_style = | material = | classification = | altitude = | namesake = | groundbreaking_date = | start_date = | stop_date = | est_completion = | completion_date = | opened_date = 1967–1983 | inauguration_date = | closing_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | cost = | ren_cost = | client = | owner = | affiliation = | height = | architectural = | structural_system = | size = | floor_count = | floor_area = | elevator_count = | grounds_area = | architect = | architecture_firm = | developer = | engineer = | known_for = | website = | embed = | embedded = | references = | footnotes = }}
The '''Slovak Radio Building''' ({{lang-sk|Budova Slovenského rozhlasu}}) is located in [[Bratislava]].
It is shaped like an upside down [[Pyramid|pyramid]]. Architects of this project were [[Štefan Svetko]], [[Štefan Ďurkovič]] and [[Barnabáš Kissling]] and it was completed in 1983. The project began in 1967. The building is 80 metres high and has a 522-seat concert hall with a large concert organ. The first test broadcast was made in 1984 and regular broadcasting began on 27 March 1985.
The building was included in a list of the 30 ugliest buildings in the world,<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/property/propertypicturegalleries/9126031/Are-these-the-ugliest-buildings-in-the-world.html?frame=2159738</ref> but has been defended by Slovak architects.<ref>http://www.thedaily.sk/slovak-radio-building-classed-among-ugliest-in-world/</ref>
