{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}} '''UCLA Center for the Study of Women''' ('''CSW''') is an organized unit at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]] and a member of the [https://web.archive.org/web/19981212031257/http://www.ncrw.org/ National Council for Research on Women]. Founded in 1984, the center works to develop and disseminate faculty and graduate student research on gender, sexuality, and women's issues through conferences, grants, seminars, and publications.<ref>{{cite web|title=Center for the Study of Women|url=http://www.ncrw.org/member-organizations/university-california-los-angeles|publisher=National Council for Research on Women|accessdate=2 August 2011}}</ref> Since its creation, CSW has sponsored hundreds of events and performances at UCLA and the surrounding Los Angeles area that pertain to gender, sexuality, and women's issues. CSW has hosted the [[academic journals]] ''[[Signs: Journal of Women in Culture and Society]]'' and ''[[Journal of Middle East Women's Studies]].''
== Organization == The Center for the Study of Women was approved as an organized research unit by the [[Regents of the University of California]] in 1984, becoming the first organized research unit in the [[University of California]] system dedicated to research on gender related issues.<ref>{{cite web|title=UCLA Center for the Study of Women|url=http://www.csw.ucla.edu/about|accessdate=21 April 2011}}</ref> The center works with UCLA's Women Studies Program to develop curriculum and promote [[feminism|feminist]] scholarship among UCLA students.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Center for Research on Women (CROW)|title=set cell vertical height University-based Research Centers on Race, Class & Gender|url=http://www.memphis.edu/crow/linksresearchcenters.htm|publisher=The University Of Memphis|accessdate=28 July 2011}}</ref>
